The official MS-Windows port homepage from gnu.org is
http://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/windows/ntemacs.html .
Many issues concerning Emacs and MS-Windows are treated there.
The page has also links to the precompiled binaries for MS-Windows of the current Emacs or earlier versions. 

If you want precompiled binaries for the latest Emacses (version 24.4 is officially released stable), please see CategoryWThirtyTwo.

Project ntemacs at (http://ntemacs.sourceforge.net/) provides clean, optimized binary builds of the latest Emacs bzr snapshot, with image support enabled and necessary dependencies bundled in the package.

== Resources ==

If you want to install Emacs on MS-Windows using a simple installer, you may have a look at the following ressources:
* [http://ntemacs.sourceforge.net/ ntemacs]
* [http://emacs-win.sourceforge.net/ emacs-win (portuguese)]
* [[EmacsW32]]
* [https://sourceforge.net/projects/emacs-bin/files/snapshots/ Latest Precompiled Emacs for Windows]

See CategoryWThirtyTwo for a lot more.

